HOUSE
RESOLUTION No. ___
Introduced by: Steuerwald
____________________________________
1 A HOUSE RESOLUTION honoring Representative
2 Michelle Davis.
3 Whereas, Representative Michelle Davis was elected in 2020
4 to serve the citizens of Indiana House District 58 and will
5 conclude her service in the Indiana House of Representatives
6 at the end of the 2026 legislative session;
7 Whereas, Representative Davis is a lifelong resident of
8 Indiana and currently resides in Whiteland;
9 Whereas, Representative Davis earned a Bachelor of Science
10 degree in Elementary Education from Ball State University and
11 a Master's degree in Curriculum and Instruction, with an
12 emphasis on Career and Technical Education, from Purdue
13 University;
20262395
HR 1522/DI 140 2026

2
1 Whereas, During her six years of service in the Indiana
2 House of Representatives, Representative Davis has served as
3 Vice Chair of the Education Committee and as a member of the
4 Commerce, Small Business and Economic Development
5 Committee, the Financial Institutions Committee, and the
6 Judiciary Committee;
7 Whereas, Beyond her legislative duties, Representative Davis
8 serves as the Director of Adult Education at Central Nine
9 Career Center and is married to her husband, James, with
10 whom she has two children, Stephanie and Nickolas;
11 Whereas, Throughout her legislative career, Representative
12 Davis has been a steadfast advocate for the education of
13 Indiana's children and has supported and advanced legislation
14 that has strengthened Indiana's reputation as a leader in
15 academic achievement;
16 Whereas, Prior to and alongside her service in the Indiana
17 General Assembly, Representative Davis has served on the
18 Region 5 Workforce Development Board and the Board of
19 Governors for the Dyslexia Institute of Indiana, and she is an
20 active member of the Indiana Association of Adult and
21 Continuing Education;
22 Whereas, Representative Davis has also been recognized as
23 a strong supporter of female athletics and female athletes,
24 having attended Ball State on a basketball scholarship and
25 being a member of the Indiana Basketball Hall of Fame;
26 Whereas, Throughout her tenure, Representative Davis has
27 demonstrated a commitment to integrity and fairness; and
28 Whereas, Representative Michelle Davis has served her
29 constituents with dedication and distinction since her election
30 to the Indiana House of Representatives: Therefore,
31 Be it resolved by the House of Representatives of the
32 General Assembly of the State of Indiana:
33 SECTION 1. That the Indiana House of Representatives
34 honors Representative Michelle Davis upon her retirement.
20262395
HR 1522/DI 140 2026

3
1 SECTION 2. That the Principal Clerk of the House of
2 Representatives shall transmit a copy of this resolution to
3 Representative Michelle Davis.
